Japan Buys Most Milling Wheat in 4 Weeks From U.S., Canada

-- B y   A y a   T a k a d a
-- 
2011-12-08T07:20:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-08/japan-buys-most-milling-wheat-in-4-weeks-from-u-s-canada-1-.html
Japan  bought 108,375 metric tons of
milling wheat from the U.S. and  Canada  in a regular tender
today, the largest volume in four weeks, the Ministry of
Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries said.  Shipment is set from Jan. 16 to Feb. 15, according to
Masafumi Otsuka at the ministry’s grain-trade division. It was
the biggest purchase since Nov. 10, when the government bought
142,032 tons.  The ministry, which controls overseas purchases and
domestic sales of wheat to stabilize supply, is  Asia ’s largest
buyer as a single entity. It has bought 3.35 million tons
through regular tenders this fiscal year, compared with 5.16
million tons in the year ended March 31.  Details of this week’s tender are listed below:  To contact the reporter on this story:
